          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-05-11 21:31:26" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>pertaining to that which is pleasing in view of its being acceptable</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>pleasing</Gloss>
                <Gloss>acceptable</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages it is necessary to restructure expressions containing ‘acceptable to’ or ‘pleasing to.’ For example, in {S:04401003500022} it may be necessary to translate ‘God accepts whoever worships him and does what is right’ or ‘God is pleased with whoever worships him and does what is right.’ Similarly, in {S:05400200300008} one may translate ‘this is good, and God our Savior likes it’ or ‘… is happy because of it.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
